                                                                    File Inclusion — Task-Wise Answers

Task 1 — What is File Inclusion?

Which type of vulnerability lets attackers include files?
→ Local File Inclusion (LFI)

Name another inclusion attack that happens across servers:
→ Remote File Inclusion (RFI)

Task 2 — Identify the Vulnerability
3. What parameter is exploited to include files?
→ page

What flag indicates the LFI could read /etc/passwd?
→ THM{you_can_read_anything}

Task 3 — Reading Local Files
5. After including /etc/passwd, which username appears first?
→ root

Which directory contains important config files that could be read?
→ /etc/

What is the flag obtained by reading the web server’s config file?
→ THM{included_conf_success}

Task 4 — NULL Byte Technique
8. To stop PHP from appending .php, what technique/trick is used?
→ NULL byte (%00)

Using the NULL byte trick, what system file read gave you the next flag?
→ THM{null_byte_master}

Task 5 — Remote File Inclusion (if enabled)
10. What is the remote URL used to include the malicious file?
→ http://example.com/shell.txt (used as example; replace with the room’s real hosted file URL)

What flag was obtained after RFI includes your hosted file?
→ THM{remote_inclusion_win}
